## ⚠️ Risks and Solutions

# Purpose:

To think ahead about possible problems during the project and define solutions that help reduce risk and keep the project realistic and achievable.

| Risk Area | What could go wrong? | How to reduce the risk (solution) |
|---|---|---|
| **Technology** | The team may face technical difficulties with telemetry integration, anomaly detection logic, machine learning tuning, or communication between system components. | Start with simple rule-based logic, keep the ML component lightweight, test each component separately, and build the system progressively instead of all at once. |
| **Timeline** | Some parts of the project, especially the aircraft or hardware integration, may take longer than expected and delay the overall progress. | Use replayed CSV scenarios in parallel so software development can continue even if the aircraft is not fully ready. Set short milestones and review progress regularly. |
| **Team** | With only two team members, workload may become unbalanced, and delays in one area could affect the whole project. | Keep the MVP focused, define responsibilities clearly, communicate regularly, and avoid adding unnecessary features outside the main scope. |
| **Testing** | Test scenarios may be too limited, and the system may not behave the same way with real data as it does with replayed scenarios. | Validate the system with multiple scenarios, compare normal and abnormal cases, and progressively move from replayed data to real telemetry when possible. |
| **Deployment** | Integration between the Guardian, database, dashboard, and aircraft telemetry may be more difficult than expected. | Fix the telemetry schema and alert schema early, test modules independently first, and connect them step by step using stable interfaces. |
| **Scope** | The project may become too broad by trying to cover too many features, systems, or advanced AI goals. | Keep the MVP limited to telemetry anomaly detection, structured alerts, and human-in-the-loop decision support. Leave advanced features for later stages. |

